('Invitation: [Code Review] [CEP] Siddhi Extension for Markov models @ Mon Aug 1, 2016 11:30am - 12:30pm (IST) (ashen@wso2.com)', 'notes i have taken. Please add anything\nmissing here.\n\n\n   - Change input parameter name "trainingBatchSize" to meaningful name\n   something which gives the information that parameter is used to enable\n   train after this amount.\n\n\n   - When checking fifth attribute do not check for\n   VariableExpressionExecutor it could be any expression executor.\n\n\n   - populateMatrix method could be called inside the constructor once\n   variables have been initialized instead of calling externally. Make\n   populateMatrix private instead of protected since its been called inside\n   only constructor.\n\n\n   - When calling processData method, no need to create new Object array\n   and assign values, just pass original array to the method.\n\n\n   - Checking currentEventTime and expiryTime calculation should not be\n   done in removeExpiredEvents method, it needs to be done in update method.\n\n\n   - Use a link Hashmap for expiredIDs instead of a using list which will\n   increase performance.\n\n\n   - In function getKey use abnormal characters instead of using , to\n   separate startState and endState which is not usually used.\n\n\n   - Remove multiplication by 1.0 which us not required when calculating\n   stateTransitionProbability.\n\n\n   - In process method add scheduler to remove expired events.\n\n\n   - Try to use get() method check for null instead of calling\n   containsCheck() in HashMaps, otherwise it needs to be checked twice.\n\n\n   - Check with MarkovChainMatirx extension implementation done for\n   analytics-apim and make sure that it could be replaced by this in next\n   release.\n\nRegards,\n\n\nOn', '   Siddhi Extension for Markov models ', 'ashen@wso2.com', '1563601974eb89b7', '1/08/2016', 'null', 'CEP', 'Q3', '2016'),
