('Invitation: [Code Review][ESB Connector] PCML Connector @ Wed Aug 31, 2016 12am - 1am (CDT) (hemika@wso2.com)', 'Notes :\nExplained the basics of using PCML to call the AS400 system and how it has\nbeen integrated into the connector.\n\n1. Removing proxy feature as it cannot be tested.\n2. Add connection pool implementation and socket properties implementation\ninto init component.\n3. Change error logs that doesn\'t break the flow to warning logs.\n4. Use handleException() method for handling exception rather than throw\nSynapseException.\n5. The static connection pool map should be thread safe.\n6. When a program call is unsuccessful, create a soap body with the AS400\nmessages that is received and then call handleException();\n7.When adding the output payload from the AS400 call to the message\ncontext, detach the existing content and add the output to the message\ncontext.\n8. Prefix objects added to message context -\nhttps://github.com/wso2-extensions/esb-connector-pcml/pull/2#discussion_r76938008\n\nPlease add if I missed anything.\n\nThanks,\nHemika\n\nHemika Kodikara\nSoftware Engineer\nWSO2 Inc.\nlean . enterprise . middleware\nhttp://wso2.com\n\nMobile : +94777688882\n\nOn', '  PCML Connector ', 'hemika@wso2.com', '156d9eeec1438f0b', '31/08/2016', 'Attendees: Elilmatha, Malaka, Thulasika, Vivekananthan, Hemika', 'ESB Connector', 'Q3', '2016'),
