('Invitation: Code Review Meeting on Log Analyzer - Improvements on art... @ Fri Jul 29, 2016 2:30pm - 3:15pm (IST) (miyurud@wso2.com)', '156267bf10ebae1c', ' Code Review Meeting on Log Analyzer - Improvements on art... ', 'biruntha@wso2.com', 'notes taken during this code review meeting below.\n\n-- \nThanks,\nMiyuru Dayarathna\nSenior Technical Lead\nMobile: +94713527783\nBlog: http://miyurublog.blogspot.com\n\n----------------------------------------\nParticipants\n-- Tharik Kanaka\n-- Sajith Ravindra\n-- Sajith Perera\n-- Sameera Ramasinghe\n-- Miyuru Dayarathna\n----------------------------------------\nPR Reviewed\nhttps://github.com/wso2/shared-analytics/pull/107\n----------------------------------------\n--TenantDomainAwareLoggingEvent\nremove line 32\nprivate static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n--TenantAwarePatternLayout.java\nNeed to address the null checks.\n\nWe should keep both tenantID and tenantDomain\nbetter to have a mapping to tenatID and tenat domain in a separate table.\nFor now we will keep tenantDomain.\nWith performance test we will do check whether its better to have\ntenatID/tenatDomain\nThis is a possible performance optimization that we can do in future.\n\nThere is a naming convention defined in "Standards and Guidelines for\nAnalytics Artifacts". Need to follow the standards and guidelines there.\nWhat we will do is once this round of fixes are done we will do one pass\nover all the code and align the names accordingly.\n\n\nOn Tue, Jul 26, 2016 at 2:44 PM, Miyuru Dayarathna <miyurud@wso2.com> wrote:\n\n> more details »\n> <https://www.google.com/calendar/event?action=VIEW&eid=Yms5dDY3cDJsNzVwMGwwbDhtczZnODNiMzAgZW5naW5lZXJpbmctZ3JvdXBAd3NvMi5jb20&tok=MTYjbWl5dXJ1ZEB3c28yLmNvbTk2MjJhMTg0M2Q3MjdiNDcwZWExMzhlNmQxMjUyODk0NTdiMjQ3M2Q&ctz=Asia/Colombo&hl=en>\n> Code Review Meeting on Log Analyzer - Improvements on artifact deployment\n> statistics, tenant domain filtering, and error code distribution\n> We will review the following PR.\n>\n> https://github.com/wso2/shared-analytics/pull/107\n> <https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Fwso2%2Fshared-analytics%2Fpull%2F107&sa=D&ust=1469528070060000&usg=AFQjCNHIpsgMkZ5m5uf57giljoXEssw53A>\n>\n> The PR is about the following improvements.\n>\n> 1. Adding scripts for artifact deplyment stats\n> 2. Tenant domain filtering instead of tenant ID\n> 3. Renaming gadgets to be matched to the new dashboard version\n> 4. Addition of the Error code distribution gadget\n>\n> *When*\n> Fri Jul 29, 2016 2:30pm – 3:15pm Colombo\n>\n> *Where*\n> LK Trace Ground Floor Meeting Room - Moria Ext:1036214 (map\n> <https://maps.google.com/maps?q=LK+Trace+Ground+Floor+Meeting+Room+-+Moria+Ext:1036214&hl=en>\n> )\n>\n> *Video call*\n> https://plus.google.com/hangouts/_/wso2.com/code-review\n> <https://plus.google.com/hangouts/_/wso2.com/code-review?hceid=bWl5dXJ1ZEB3c28yLmNvbQ.bk9t67p2l75p0l0l8ms6g83b30>\n>\n> *Calendar*\n> miyurud@wso2.com\n>\n> *Who*\n> •\n> Miyuru Dayarathna - organizer\n> •\n> Tharik Kanaka\n> •\n> Buddhima Wijeweera\n> •\n> sameerar@wso2.com\n> •\n> WSO2 Engineering Group\n> •\n> Sajith Perera\n> •\n> Sajith Ravindra\n>\n> Going?   *Yes\n> <https://www.google.com/calendar/event?action=RESPOND&eid=Yms5dDY3cDJsNzVwMGwwbDhtczZnODNiMzAgZW5naW5lZXJpbmctZ3JvdXBAd3NvMi5jb20&rst=1&tok=MTYjbWl5dXJ1ZEB3c28yLmNvbTk2MjJhMTg0M2Q3MjdiNDcwZWExMzhlNmQxMjUyODk0NTdiMjQ3M2Q&ctz=Asia/Colombo&hl=en>\n> - Maybe\n> <https://www.google.com/calendar/event?action=RESPOND&eid=Yms5dDY3cDJsNzVwMGwwbDhtczZnODNiMzAgZW5naW5lZXJpbmctZ3JvdXBAd3NvMi5jb20&rst=3&tok=MTYjbWl5dXJ1ZEB3c28yLmNvbTk2MjJhMTg0M2Q3MjdiNDcwZWExMzhlNmQxMjUyODk0NTdiMjQ3M2Q&ctz=Asia/Colombo&hl=en>\n> - No\n> <https://www.google.com/calendar/event?action=RESPOND&eid=Yms5dDY3cDJsNzVwMGwwbDhtczZnODNiMzAgZW5naW5lZXJpbmctZ3JvdXBAd3NvMi5jb20&rst=2&tok=MTYjbWl5dXJ1ZEB3c28yLmNvbTk2MjJhMTg0M2Q3MjdiNDcwZWExMzhlNmQxMjUyODk0NTdiMjQ3M2Q&ctz=Asia/Colombo&hl=en>*\n>     more options »\n> <https://www.google.com/calend