('Invitation: Code Review : Amazon SQS inbound endpoint @ Tue Sep 20, 2016 2:30pm - 3pm (IST) (biruntha@wso2.com)', '157464e33ebc2b02', ' Code Review  Amazon SQS inbound endpoint ', 'biruntha@wso2.com', 'notes below,\n\nDate: 20 September 2016\n\nParticipants: Malaka, PET team\n\nContributor: Biruntha\n\nComments:\n\n   -\n\n   If destination, accessKey , secretKey is empty, need to handle that.\n   -\n\n   Before put the debug log, need to check isDebugEnabled().\n   -\n\n   Check whether receiveMessageRequest object can be reused or not.\n   -\n\n   To check messages list is empty or not, use isEmpty() rather than\nusing size()\n   != 0.\n   -\n\n   Check injectingSeq != null this is done on the parent class . If it is\n   not, need to done from the constructor.\n   -\n\n   Check what are the message attributes can be handle in Amazon sqs.\n   -\n\n   Need to run the inbound in the clustering environment.\n   -\n\n   Need to include the rollbacking concept like JMS.\n   -\n\n   When one consumer delete the message after consuming from the queue,\n   other consumer can’t consume that  particular message. Provide proper\n   solution for that.\n\n\nThanks,\n\nBiruntha\n\nAssociate Software Engineer\nWSO2\nEmail : biruntha@wso2.com\nLinkedin : https://lk.linkedin.com/in/biruntha\nMobile : +94773718986\n\nOn', 'Participants: Malaka, PET team', '20/09/2016', 'undefined', 'Q3', '2016'),
