('Invitation: [Code Review] Identity Cloud On Premise Agent @ Fri Sep 23, 2016 2pm - 3pm (IST) (Identity Management & Security)', '1575307224612658', '  Identity Cloud On Premise Agent ', '', 'notes below.\n\n\nATTENDEES\n\nLakshan, Darshana, Vindula, Dinusha, Rushmin, Godwin, Maduranga, Ishara\n\n\nNOTES\n\n\n   1. "Limit" query parameter should be optional in getUserList, if there\n   is no limit parameter in the request, need to get users according to the\n   configurable amount of limits\n   2. User Store manager should be pluggable. (Should able to configure\n   JDBC User store manager)\n   3. Support secure LDAP(ldaps) communication\n   4. Do an in memory Cache implementation in agent\n   5. Add a context for rest service (Ex. https://localhost:8080/\n   *useragent/*authenticate)\n   6. Handle exception properly and send error code when exception occurs\n   in rest service\n   7. Remove catching general Exception and catch exact Exception\n   8. Return user attribute with User object with Property Map when get\n   user attributes.\n   9. Fix formatting issues\n   10. Add meaningful debug messages\n   11. Use C5 CheckStyle plugin to validate the code\n   12. Add Class/method level comments\n   13. Have a separate meeting to discuss the code duplication of user core.\n   14. Remove magic words and put into constant. Ex/. "#" should be a\n   constant in LDAP User store manager\n   15. Define API (Swagger)\n   16. Brainstorm and check how to use Cipher tool without giving user to\n   run additional scripts.\n\nThanks\nGodwin\n\n\n\nOn Thu, Sep 22, 2016 at 11:22 PM, Lakshan Gamage <lakshan@wso2.com> wrote:\n\n> more details »\n> <https://www.google.com/calendar/event?action=VIEW&eid=NGVkZzQ0NXFzbGIycGlya2JqbGNxMXBvb2MgZW5naW5lZXJpbmctZ3JvdXBAd3NvMi5jb20&tok=NjEjd3NvMi5jb21fYThsdmhkMW9vZmZ1azNwNzJsN29lcjFyOW9AZ3JvdXAuY2FsZW5kYXIuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbTFiMTk1N2VmZjNmMmRjZjhhNDBhNWFhMTUzYjQ3Y2Q2OWEzOGZhNTQ&ctz=Asia/Colombo&hl=en>\n> [Code Review] Identity Cloud On', 'null', '23/09/2016', 'undefined', 'Q3', '2016'),
