('Invitation: Code review - Billing core and billing vendor implementat... @ Mon Sep 26, 2016 4:30pm - 5:30pm (IST) (sithuminis@wso2.com)', '157659346392ce44', ' Code review - Billing core and billing vendor implementat... ', 'sithuminis@wso2.com', 'notes,\n\n*Code Level Changes*\n\n   - Change the interface name CloudBillingCore as CloudBiliing.\n   - Stripeutils name also should change to stripeCloudBilling.\n   - In APICloudUtils class rename the getters and setters to the proper\n   name.\n   - Remove the debug log in the getConfigInJson where it print the whole\n   config file.\n   - Rename the  package name to org.wso2.carbon.cloud.billing.vendor.stripe\n\n*XML Changes *\n\n   - Vendor className should be added to the billing core xml file.\n   - SSLRelyingParty element should be change to SSLConfig\n   - Remove the unwanted keys mention in the vendor config.\n\n\n*Important notes*\n\n   - When using stripe, two customers using the monetization feature there\n   will be an issue in using multiple keys(setting Stripe keys using SDK).\n   Can use the way of sending the keys with the rest call itself.\n   - LoadBillingVendorUtilClass - Should only happen in the bundle\n   activation, to get the billing vendor class the instance.\n   - Billing vendor config and core configs should be taken in bundle\n   activation.\n\n\n*Pending Action Items*\n\n   - Need to finalize the billing core xml file, in the more generalized\n   manner for all the clouds(E.g API Cloud, APP cloud ..).\n\n\nPlease feel free to add anything I missed.\n\nBest Regards,\n~Vinuri~\n\nOn', 'null', '26/09/2016', 'undefined', 'Q3', '2016'),
('Invitation: Code Review : AmazonSQS inbound endpoint @ Tue Sep 27, 2016 1:30pm - 2pm (IST) (biruntha@wso2.com)', '15769c6fc65541ee', ' Code Review  AmazonSQS inbound endpoint ', 'biruntha@wso2.com', 'notes below,\n\nDate: 27 September 2016\n\nParticipants: Malaka, Pamod\n\nContributor: Biruntha\n\nComments:\n\n   -\n\n   Do R&D for Using JMS with amazon SQS\n   -\n\n   Study the AWS-SDK-JAVA, how it is communicating with the Amazon SQS\n   -\n\n   Check whether selector option is available or not\n   -\n\n   Check with sqs connector to send message to the queue\n   -\n\n   Get content type for the message from the user through the message\n   attribute and if it is not specified set as default (text/plain).\n   -\n\n   Add the type of inbound whether polling or listening or event based in\n   documentation\n   -\n\n   Put class level comments to describe about AmazonSQSPollingConsumer\n   -\n\n   Put description for each parameter used\n   -\n\n   Initialize the accessKey, secretKey within the constructor\n   -\n\n   Put info log at start to identify the inbound is started\n   -\n\n   Put debug log with meaningful to identify which inbound is started\n   -\n\n   Don’t throw QueueDoesNotExistException, AmazonSQSException. Try to use\n   SynapseException\n   -\n\n   After loading all the parameters, Put one debug log with the values for\n   each parameters.\n   -\n\n   Create credentials for the client from the constructor.\n   -\n\n   While receiving the message from queue, get the attribute name from the\n   user\n   -\n\n   For injectMessage method, give proper name for variables, use specific\n   exceptions\n\n\nThanks,\n\nBiruntha\n\nAssociate Software Engineer\nWSO2\nEmail : biruntha@wso2.com\nLinkedin : https://lk.linkedin.com/in/biruntha\nMobile : +94773718986\n\nOn', 'Participants: Malaka, Pamod', '27/09/2016', 'undefined', 'Q3', '2016'),
